<!-- ============================================
     FAQ
     ============================================ -->
<section class="sponsor-faq">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="sponsor-faq-header">
      <span class="label label--accent reveal">Questions</span>
      <h2 class="sponsor-faq-title reveal">Frequently Asked</h2>
    </div>

    <div class="sponsor-faq-grid">
      <div class="sponsor-faq-item reveal">
        <h3 class="sponsor-faq-question">What makes AI TownSquare different from other AI events?</h3>
        <p class="sponsor-faq-answer">AI TownSquare is not an event—it's civic infrastructure. We use a rigorous 7-phase protocol derived from Socratic method, scientific inquiry, and deliberative democracy. Every session produces a published Civic Brief within 48 hours that feeds the Societal Readiness Index. This is structured knowledge creation, not networking.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="sponsor-faq-item reveal reveal-d1">
        <h3 class="sponsor-faq-question">How are participants selected?</h3>
        <p class="sponsor-faq-answer">We curate for cross-sector diversity. Each session includes healthcare professionals, financial regulators, government officials, technology executives, academics, and engaged citizens. The diversity is the engine of insight—homogeneous groups produce predictable answers.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="sponsor-faq-item reveal reveal-d2">
        <h3 class="sponsor-faq-question">What is the Societal Readiness Index?</h3>
        <p class="sponsor-faq-answer">The SRI is a six-pillar benchmark measuring how prepared societies are for AI integration. It aggregates qualitative civic data from TownSquare sessions with quantitative policy and infrastructure metrics. Partners receive early access to SRI updates before public release.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="sponsor-faq-item reveal reveal-d3">
        <h3 class="sponsor-faq-question">Can we propose session topics?</h3>
        <p class="sponsor-faq-answer">Founding Partners have input on the questions we examine. All questions must pass three tests: (1) No single expert can answer alone, (2) It affects multiple sectors differently, (3) Reasonable people disagree. We don't do promotional sessions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="sponsor-faq-item reveal reveal-d4">
        <h3 class="sponsor-faq-question">What's the geographic footprint?</h3>
        <p class="sponsor-faq-answer">2026 sessions are planned for Dubai, Doha, Singapore, London, New York, and San Francisco. Partners receive presence across all sessions at their tier level. We're building global civic infrastructure, not regional events.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="sponsor-faq-item reveal reveal-d5">
        <h3 class="sponsor-faq-question">How long are partnership terms?</h3>
        <p class="sponsor-faq-answer">Annual partnerships with renewal options. Founding Partners receive permanent "Founding Partner" designation regardless of renewal—your early support is recognized in perpetuity.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

